research science and challenge the existing paradigm where not enough women
play leading roles alongside their male counterparts. </span><span style="background-color: transparent; letter-spacing: inherit; line-height: 18pt;">This event is set only a
few weeks after the International Day of Women and Girls in Science Celebrated
annually on 11th February and serves as acknowledgement of the progress made in
